A rapist – who is the cousin of the victim – has been sentenced to 18 years for his crimes. 
Police spokesperson Captain Nqobile Gwala said in a statement that the Mthunzini Regional Court had convicted and sentenced the 35-year-old on December 12, 2017 after the court heard details of the incident in which the 18-year-old woman was brutally raped and stabbed in the Esikhaleni area outside Richards Bay.
The name of the accused is being withheld to protect the identity of the victim.
READ: Man gets life imprisonment for rape
Gwala said that on April 3, the victim had been at her place of residence coming from a nearby tavern in Mandlankala, Esikhaleni. 
“She was with her cousin who allegedly threatened her with a knife and raped her. She was also stabbed (repeatedly). The victim managed to escape and a case of rape was opened at Esikhaleni police station.”
The docket was transferred to Empangeni Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences unit for further investigation. 
READ: Man receives three life terms for rape and murder
“The next day the accused was arrested and charged for rape. He appeared in court several times until he was convicted and sentence by Mthunzini Regional Court.”
KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner, Major General Bheki Langa welcomed the sentenced handed down to the accused.
